rComments: Professor Cunha is probably the least helpful english teacher/prof I've ever had. She's never organized and her lectures are quite boring. Her assignments were weird and they expected a lot out of nothing because they never taught half of the things we needed to succeed in the course.

Professor Cunha is extremely unorganized and is not very good at teaching any academic material. She should go teach at a high school, where she would be much better suited with her level of organization and teaching. I wish there had been reviews on her before I had enrolled in her course because I will never take one of her courses again.

Cunha is like everyone's dreaded high school English teacher. She constantly gives assignments and does DGDs where she checks attendance. Her class is easy to pass and she is very nice so I can't complain much, but would definitely not recommend her if you don't like reading and writing like me.

rComments: She's a great person but her grading is not a very clear scale of criteria. it is also very hard to understand what she is teaching because you goes back and forth between many topics

Prof. Cunha is often unorganized but overall a good instructor. It feels like a HS class. It was not difficult at all. As long as you attend her discussion groups AND lectures, you'll do fine. I recommend seeing her during office hours to go over essay drafts. When it comes to readings, you only need to skim over the essays for the DGD activities.
She gives so many assignments as compared to other professors
